==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Protosulphide
<hw>Pro`to*sul"phide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Proto-</ets> + <ets>sulphide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>That one of a series of sulphides of any element which has the
lowest proportion of sulphur; a sulphide with but one atom of sulphur in
the molecule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protosulphuret</ent>⟦br⟧
